        <!-- Logo at the top -->

        <h1>Congratulations! Your order has been successfully placed.</h1>
        <img src="https://api.metabolixmd.com/image/4.png" alt="MetabolixMD Logo" class="logo">

        <p>Thank you <b> <%= customerName %></b> for reaching out to <span class="highlight">MetabolixMD</span>! We’re excited to help you on your path to a healthier you. Our personalized weight loss programs are designed to provide the guidance, support, and medical expertise you need to reach your goals. With options including medications like <em>semaglutide</em> and <em>tirzepatide</em>, tailored nutrition plans, and regular consultations, we’re here to help you succeed safely and effectively.</p>

        <p>Our team will reach out soon to schedule your initial consultation. In the meantime, please feel free to email us for further queries at <span class="contact-info"><a href="mailto:consultant@metabolixmd.com">consultant@metabolixmd.com</a></span>.</p>

        <hr>

        <h2>Here are a few tips to keep in mind while on medication</h2>

        <div class="tips">
            <h3>Small, frequent meals</h3>
            <p>Start with smaller portions spread throughout the day to ease nausea and digestion, common in the first month of tirzepatide use.</p>

            <h3>Focus on protein</h3>
            <p>Prioritize lean proteins like chicken, fish, or tofu to maintain muscle mass and aid satiety while reducing overall calorie intake.</p>

            <h3>Choose fiber-rich foods</h3>
            <p>Incorporate vegetables, fruits, and whole grains to promote digestion and reduce constipation, a possible side effect of GLP-1 drugs.</p>

            <h3>Stay hydrated</h3>
            <p>Drink plenty of water (8-10 glasses a day) to help with digestion and manage potential side effects like nausea or bloating.</p>

            <h3>Avoid greasy or fatty foods</h3>
            <p>High-fat meals can increase nausea and stomach discomfort, so opt for lighter, low-fat options to reduce gastrointestinal issues.</p>

            <h3>Limit sugar intake</h3>
            <p>Avoid sugary foods and beverages as they can spike blood sugar and counteract the appetite-controlling effects of tirzepatide.</p>

            <h3>Incorporate healthy fats</h3>
            <p>Add small amounts of healthy fats like avocados, nuts, and olive oil to your meals to promote fullness without overwhelming digestion.</p>

            <h3>Monitor portion sizes</h3>
            <p>Keep portions moderate to avoid overwhelming the stomach, which may already be slowed by tirzepatide, leading to discomfort.</p>

            <h3>Eat slowly and mindfully</h3>
            <p>Chewing slowly and savoring meals can help prevent overeating and aid digestion, which is important while adjusting to GLP-1 medications.</p>

            <h3>Limit alcohol consumption</h3>
            <p>Alcohol can irritate the stomach and interfere with blood sugar regulation, so limit intake to avoid worsening side effects.</p>
        </div>

        <hr>

